<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-06T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-06T17:00:00-05:00" n="492" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d492">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1165a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Gonzales</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-06T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 6, 1917—5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s March 2, 4 p.m. In view of great necessity felt by sugar
                            mills, mining companies and other enterprises for continuing operations
                            and as these properties are dependent upon their coal and other supplies
                            from the united States it would seem imperative that the Cuban
                            Government allow vessels containing such supplies to pass through the
                            blockade, it being understood that assurances would be given that such
                            supplies were to be delivered directly to American interests and that
                            they should in no way be transferred to any persons under arms against
                            the Government of Cuba.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>